      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VITE MONET (8) was first up for close to six months when 4.4 metres away in third at Menangle last start. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but he has won three of five previous second up attempts so should be improved and scored the only time he raced here. JORGE STREET (9) won twice in a row at this venue before he worked and finished fourth last start. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Leading hope. LOYALIST NZ (10) has been struggling to find his best but drops in grade off his last attempt in the city and has won here before. HEZ DUSTY (5) is worth plenty of thought backing up off a win by 3.5 metres from a similar barrier at Goulburn on Monday.",
